WEEK 9 ANSWERS
. The Industrial Revolution and Societal Transformation:
The Industrial Revolution of the 18th and 19th centuries ushered in a period of profound societal change. Technological advancements in manufacturing, transportation, and communication reshaped economies and ways of life. While it brought about unprecedented economic growth, it also led to social and environmental challenges, including labor exploitation and pollution. Understanding the lessons from this era can inform discussions on how to navigate the benefits and drawbacks of technological progress in the modern world.
